lexUnit.name: swing.v
lexUnit.definition: FN: move or cause to move back and forth or from side to side

sentence.text: Tug swung his arms like windmills .
Do your shoulders creak if you swing your arms round in circles ?
Swing your arms the opposite way to your legs .
They sang on the road and swung their arms .
She swung her arms above her head and cracked her hand on a low beam .
Gabriel swung his arms .
And he shivered energetically and swung his arms and clapped his shoulders .
She swung her head in his direction .
Len now swung his head to the side .
He swung his head like an animal that suddenly intuits a reason for fear .
He swung his head from side to side .
When the driver swung his head to face her , he shrugged and the man 's features cracked into a smile of false teeth .
He had swung his head round , glaring at me , his eyes hard as glass .
Furious , she swung her head away , not knowing what to answer .
A gleaming white horse stopped eating from the manger and swung his head towards me , whickering a little .
Flex the foot and swing the leg forwards and backwards 5 times .
As the youth in the crash-helmet doubled over , Quinn hoisted him off his machine , swung his own right leg over it , engaged gear and gunned the engine .
Conscious of being looked at she swung her legs and smiled faintly , twitching her shoulders and arching her neck .
Marler , five feet seven , perched his backside on Paula 's desk and swung his legs .
She swung her shapely legs inside and began talking as he switched on the ignition .
Fearon swung his legs to the floor , put his hands on the edge of the bed and grimaced up at her .
She handed him his denim jacket and swung her legs out of the car .
When he realised his mammy was at the door , he swung his legs out of the chair and came rushing to greet her .
Painfully , Christine swung her legs to one side until she was in a sitting position .
As it does so , it swings its body slightly from side to side , like a machine-gunner raking the enemy ranks .
She swung herself lightly from the jeep and walked slowly alongside the pool .
Despite fitzAlan 's assurances that she would n't encounter a corpse , she held her breath with trepidation every time she swung her free hand in a groping semicircle .
He sheathed the hologram blade , then , with a hand pressed against the bunched shoulder muscles , swung his left arm in a wide overhead circle .
Tabitha swung her feet to the floor .
Without thought , Theda threw off the covers and swung her feet to the floor .
Shelley suddenly swung his luminous face towards me , sat quickly down on a chair , sticking out one leg and resting a hand on his thigh , clearly inviting me to hold the floor awhile .
Delaney swung a foot on to the ladder .
He swung himself around the turn at the bottom of the stairs and raced blindly along the lower corridor .
Trent swung himself over to the settee so that she would n't have to shout .
Jimmy swung himself down , and lifted the shopping bag out of the cart .
The horse slacked his pace , swung his neck down to ease the tension in it , and relaxed his tail .
He gave a brief nod , and swung himself down the companionway .
Ian shook himself free from his bunk , pulled on his flannels and swung himself up the companionway and on to the deck .
Her loose hair swung forward and enclosed her face like a pair of golden doors .
I saw Sophie swing lithely on to a bus before it stopped moving .
She swung round , surprised and a little wary .
The king swung round .
